Package gov.nasa.larcfm.IO

Class ConfigReader

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.nasa.larcfm.IO.ConfigReader
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ErrorReporter, ParameterProvider, ParameterReader
    public final class ConfigReader
extends java.lang.Object
implements ParameterReader, ParameterProvider, ErrorReporter

    This object will read in and store a set of configuration parameters. The parameters can be listed in the conventional way, such as: param = 10 [NM]. In addition, the parameters can be listed in a table format: 

     param1 param2 param3
 1      5      100
 2      10     99 
 3      20     98
 4      10     97
 5      5      96

    If the parameters are stored in this way, then every call to the "next()" method will update the parameters (for this example, the parameters: param1, param2, and param3) with the next values in the file.

    Instead of next(), the nextIterate() method can be called which will return all of the param1 values with each of the param2 values, and so on. In this case the parameters may require different numbers of values; so, the columns of values should be augmented with an invalid value that will be ignored, for example

     param1 param2 param3
 1      5      100
 2      10     99 
 3      20     x
 4      x      x
 5      x      x

    A special parameter called "importConfigFile = file.cfg" will read the parameters from that file and include those parameters as if they were parameters in this file. The file imported may also have an "importConfigFile" option. Only one importConfigFile option is allowed per file. Parameters read from a secondary file will not overwrite parameters set in their parent file.

    It is possible to programmatically add additional import keys to a reader through the addIncludeName() method, allowing for multiple potential imports per file. The key importConfigFile is always first in the list of imports read, with others read in the order the keys were added.

        public void addIncludeName​(java.lang.String name)
        Add an additional import key to this reader. If the file read contains this key, the reader will interpret its value as a file name to be imported. Files are imported in the order these keys were defined. In the case of import duplication, the earlier definitions will take precedence.
        Parameters:
        name - new import directive key

        public void setCaseSensitive​(boolean b)
        If set to true, headers and parameter keys will be stored in their input case. If set to false, headers and parameter keys will be stored in lower case. This should not affect ParameterData behavior, but it may make header matching more picky. Defaults to false.
